Pre-Game Insights: Cyprus and Lithuania will meet in Limassol for a friendly match, concluding their Euro 2024 qualifying campaigns.
Cyprus endured a disappointing Euro 2024 qualifying run, suffering an 8th consecutive defeat against Spain with a 3-1 loss.
Lithuania had a better qualifying campaign, securing their position above Bulgaria in their group.
Cyprus manager Ketsbaia might experiment with the lineup but could call upon key players like Grigoris Kastanos.
Lithuania will miss Eligijus Jankauskas and Paulius Golubickas due to injuries.
Predicting a 1-1 draw, considering Lithuania’s struggles away from home and Cyprus’s determination to end on a positive note.
